ow frontend and backend components work together and improved my ability to debug issues across the full stack and deliver end-to-end features efficiently.\"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"That sounds like a great full-stack project! You mentioned handling user authentication\\u2014could you elaborate on how you implemented authentication in this project? For example, did you use JWT, sessions, or another method?\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Thank you. One project I\\u2019d like to highlight is a web-based application I worked on where I handled both the frontend and backend development.\\r\\n\\r\\nMy role involved understanding the requirements, designing the database structure, and implementing the complete workflow of the application. On the backend, I was responsible for building the core business logic, handling data validation, managing user authentication, and integrating the database.\\r\\n\\r\\nOn the frontend, I worked on creating responsive user interfaces, integrating forms with backend services, and ensuring smooth user interactions. I also collaborated with designers to convert static designs into functional pages and made sure the application worked well across devices.\\r\\n\\r\\nThis project helped me understand how frontend and backend components work together and improved my ability to debug issues across the full stack and deliver end-to-end features efficiently.\"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"Got it! Let me circle back to authentication since it\\u2019s a key part of full-stack development. You mentioned managing user authentication\\u2014could you share which library or approach you used for this? For example, did you implement JWT, OAuth, or something else?\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"We used a basic session-based authentication approach where user sessions were created after login and validated for protected routes. I handled login validation and access control logic\"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"Th